        <text x="95" y="17" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--text-muted, #6B7280); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="9">~7B parameters</text>
        <!-- Plus sign -->
        <text x="195" y="100" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--text, #0F1117); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="20" font-weight="700">+</text>
        <!-- B matrix -->
        <rect x="220" y="30" width="50" height="130" rx="5" style="fill: var(--blue-9, #D5F5FD); stroke: var(--accent, #2D8ABF);" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="245" y="85" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--accent-dark, #1E5A8A); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="13" font-weight="700">B</text>
        <text x="245" y="105" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--accent-dark, #1E5A8A); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="8.5">d &times; r</text>
        <!-- Multiply sign -->
        <text x="284" y="100" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--text, #0F1117); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="14" font-weight="700">&times;</text>
        <!-- A matrix -->
        <rect x="298" y="55" width="130" height="50" rx="5" style="fill: var(--blue-8, #B0ECF9); stroke: var(--accent, #2D8ABF);" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="363" y="78" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--accent-dark, #1E5A8A); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="13" font-weight="700">A</text>
        <text x="363" y="95" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--accent-dark, #1E5A8A); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="8.5">r &times; d</text>
        <!-- Label for trainable -->
        <text x="310" y="133" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--accent, #2D8ABF); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="8.5" font-weight="600">TRAINABLE</text>
        <text x="310" y="148" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--accent, #2D8ABF); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="9">~10M parameters</text>
        <!-- Equals sign -->
        <text x="455" y="100" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--text, #0F1117); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="20" font-weight="700">=</text>
        <!-- Result W' -->
        <rect x="475" y="55" width="55" height="55" rx="6" style="fill: var(--accent, #2D8ABF);"/>
        <text x="502" y="87" text-anchor="middle" fill="white" style="font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="14" font-weight="700">W&rsquo;</text>
        <!-- Rank annotation -->
        <text x="310" y="185" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--text-muted, #6B7280); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="9" font-style="italic">r = 8&ndash;64 (typical) vs. d = 4096+ (attention hidden dimension)</text>
        <text x="310" y="200" text-anchor="middle" style="fill: var(--text-muted, #6B7280); font-family: var(--font-body);" font-size="9" font-style="italic">Adapters are injected into each attention layer&rsquo;s Q, K, V, O projections</text>
      </svg>
      <p class="visual-diagram__caption">
        LoRA injects small trainable matrices into the frozen model. The rank
        <em>r</em> controls the trade-off between expressiveness and
        efficiency. Higher rank captures more complex adaptations but uses
        more memory. Illustrative diagram; dimensions are not to scale.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p>
      The calculator below lets you explore how model size and LoRA rank
      affect the number of trainable parameters, memory requirements, and
      hardware feasibility. Try the presets to see realistic configurations,
      then adjust the sliders to match your own setup.
    </p>

    <!-- LoRA Calculator (interactive) -->
<div class="lora-widget" id="lora-widget">
  <div class="lora-widget__title">LoRA Parameter Calculator</div>
  <div class="lora-widget__subtitle">
    Adjust model size and LoRA rank to see how many parameters you actually train,
    how much memory you need, and what hardware can run it.
  </div>

  <div class="lora-presets" id="lora-presets">
    <button class="lora-pre-btn lora-pre-btn--active" data-idx="0">Qwen 3 4B (Colab T4)</button>
    <button class="lora-pre-btn" data-idx="1">Gemma 3 12B</button>
    <button class="lora-pre-btn" data-idx="2">Qwen 3 32B</button>
    <button class="lora-pre-btn" data-idx="3">Llama 3.3 70B</button>
    <button class="lora-pre-btn" data-idx="4">DeBERTa (encoder)</button>
  </div>

  <div class="lora-grid">
    <!-- Left: Controls -->
    <div class="lora-controls">
      <div class="lora-controls__label">Configuration</div>

      <div class="lora-slider">
