        <strong>Ornstein et al. (2023),</strong>
        <a href="https://doi.org/10.1017/pan.2024.2" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>How to Train Your Stochastic Parrot: Large Language Models for Political Texts.</em></a>
        The closest thing to a practitioner&rsquo;s handbook for the full
        pipeline covered in this module. Covers prompt design, validation
        workflows, cost management, and the transition from interactive
        exploration to research-grade annotation. If you read one paper
        from today&rsquo;s session, make it this one.
      </p>
    </div>

